
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-sivabalan-pce-disco-stateful-03.txt'>
    <title>"IGP Extensions for Stateful PCE Discovery", Siva Sivabalan, Jan Medved, Xian Zhang</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-sivabalan-pce-disco-stateful-03.txt</link>
    <description>When a PCE is a Label Switching Router (LSR) participating in the Interior Gateway Protocol (IGP), or even a server participating in IGP, its presence and path computation capabilities can be advertised using IGP flooding.  Such IGP extensions exist for OSPF and ISIS. This document specifies two new PCE capabilities advertised by IGP.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-01-12T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
